Sun Apr 26 09:39:39 UTC 2026 - Dirk Müller <dmueller@suse.com>

- update to 1.1.1:
  * Fix SafeMIMEText.set_payload() crash on Python 3.13 (#80).
  * Add configuration key `MAIL_SEND_OPTIONS` to support setting
    `mail_options` for `smtplib.SMTP.send_mail`
  * (e.g. `SMTPUTF8`) (#61).
  * Pre-encodes FQDN str with punycode to improve compatibility
    (#66).
  * Migrates as many as possible test cases from Django mail
    module (#64).
  * Improve way of populating smtp key/cert to avoid TypeError in
    py>=12 (#68).

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Mon Jan 22 22:39:52 UTC 2024 - Dirk Müller <dmueller@suse.com>

- update to 1.0.0:
  * Drop Python 3.6 support.
  * Fix compatibility issue with Python 3.10
  * Fix the log file generation issue to ensure that the log
    filename is random
  * Fix compatibility issue with Python 3.12
  * Support passing `from_email` in tuple format to `send_mail()`
    function

